021import static org.tquadrat.foundation.lang.Objects.requireNonNullArgument;
022
023import org.apiguardian.api.API;
024import org.tquadrat.foundation.annotation.ClassVersion;
025import javafx.event.Event;
026import javafx.event.EventHandler;
027import javafx.event.EventType;
028import javafx.scene.Node;
029import javafx.scene.control.Alert;
030import javafx.scene.control.Alert.AlertType;

038/**
039 *  This class provides a fluent API to build an
040 *  {@link Alert}.
041 *
042 *  @extauthor Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
043 *  @version $Id: AlertBuilder.java 1095 2024-02-06 17:30:48Z tquadrat $
044 *  @since 0.4.1
045 *
046 *  @UMLGraph.link
047 */
048@SuppressWarnings( "ClassWithTooManyMethods" )
049@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: AlertBuilder.java 1095 2024-02-06 17:30:48Z tquadrat $" )
050@API( status = STABLE, since = "0.4.1" )
051public class AlertBuilder
052{
053        /*------------*\
054    ====** Attributes **=======================================================
055        \*------------*/
056    /**
057     *  The alert instance to build.
058     */
059    private final Alert m_Alert;
060
061    /**
062     *  Flag that prevents the re-use of the builder.
063     */
064    private boolean m_IsBuilt;
065
066        /*--------------*\
067    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
068        \*--------------*/
069    /**
070     *  Creates a new instance of {@code AlertBuilder}.
071     *
072     *  @param  type    The type of the new alert.
073     */
074    public AlertBuilder( final AlertType type )
075    {
076        m_Alert = new Alert( requireNonNullArgument( type, "type" ) );
077        m_IsBuilt = false;
078    }   //  AlertBuilder()
079
080        /*---------*\
081    ====** Methods **==========================================================
082        \*---------*/
083    /**
084     *  <p>{@summary Registers an event filter for the new alert.}</p>
085     *
086     *  @param  <E> The event class of the filer.
087     *  @param  eventType   The type of the events received by the filter.
088     *  @param  eventFilter The event filter.
089     *  @return The builder reference.
090     *
091     *  @see Alert#addEventFilter(EventType,EventHandler)
092     */
093    public final <E extends Event> AlertBuilder addEventFilter( final EventType<E> eventType, final EventHandler<? super E> eventFilter )
094    {
095        checkIsBuilt();
096        m_Alert.addEventFilter( eventType, eventFilter );
097
098        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
099        return this;
100    }   //  addEventFilter()
101
102    /**
103     *  <p>{@summary Registers an even filter for the new alert.}</p>
104     *
105     *  @param  <E> The event class of the filer.
106     *  @param  eventType   The type of the events received by the filter.
107     *  @param  eventHandler    The event handler.
108     *  @return The builder reference.
109     *
110     *  @see Alert#addEventHandler(EventType,EventHandler)
111     */
112    public final <E extends Event> AlertBuilder addEventHandler( final EventType<E> eventType, final EventHandler<? super E> eventHandler )
113    {
114        checkIsBuilt();
115        m_Alert.addEventHandler( eventType, eventHandler );
116
117        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
118        return this;
119    }   //  addEventFilter()
120
121    /**
122     *  Returns the alert instance.
123     *
124     *  @return The alert.
125     */
126    public final Alert build()
127    {
128        checkIsBuilt();
129        m_IsBuilt = true;
130
131        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
132        return m_Alert;
133    }   //  build()
134
135    /**
136     *  Throws an
137     *  {@link IllegalStateException}
138     *  when
139     *  {@link #m_IsBuilt}
140     *  is {@code true}.
141     *
142     *  @throws IllegalStateException
143     *      {@link #m_IsBuilt}
144     *      is @code true}.
145     */
146    private final void checkIsBuilt() throws IllegalStateException
147    {
148        if( m_IsBuilt ) throw new IllegalStateException( "Illegal Builder state" );
149    }   //  checkIsBuilt()
150
151    /**
152     *  <p>{@summary Sets the content text for the new alert.}</p>
153     *  <p>This operation can be called repeatedly; each consecutive call will
154     *  overwrite the value set by the previous one.</p>
155     *
156     *  @param  s   The content text; can be {@code null}.
157     *  @return The builder reference.
158     *
159     *  @see Alert#setContentText(String)
160     */
161    public final AlertBuilder setContentText( final String s )
162    {
163        checkIsBuilt();
164        m_Alert.setContentText( s );
165
166        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
167        return this;
168    }   //  setContentText()
169

189    }   //  setDialogPane()

195     *
196     *  @param  width   The window width.

198     *  @return The builder reference.
199     *
200     *  @see Alert#setHeight(double)
201     *  @see Alert#setWidth(double)
202     */
203    public final AlertBuilder setDimensions( final double width, final double height )
204    {
205        setHeight( height );
206        setWidth( width );
207
208        //---* Done *----------------------------------------------------------
209        return this;
210    }   //  setDimensions()

405    /**
406     *  <p>{@summary Sets the flag that indicates whether the window for the

408     *  <p>This operation can be called repeatedly; each consecutive call will
409     *  overwrite the value set by the previous one.</p>
410     *
411     *  @param  flag    {@code true} for a resizeable window, _false for a
412     *      window with fixed sizes.
413     *  @return The builder reference.
414     *

416     */
417    public final AlertBuilder setResizable( final boolean flag )
